Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 New Creek Wind, LLC Reactive Power Compensation
NEW CREEK WIND, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
New Creek Wind, LLC ("New Creek") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the New Creek generating facility ("New Creek Facility").
The New Creek Facility is a wind turbine generating facility located in Grant County, West Virginia. The New Creek Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Virginia Electric and Power Company and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth New Creek's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the New Creek Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
New Creek's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to New Creek shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $412,999.92. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $34,416.66.
